  "prompt": "Does Volkswagen Passat 2004 have the AUX port?",
  "response": "The 2004 Volkswagen Passat does not typically come equipped with an AUX port as a standard feature. Most vehicles from that era did not include AUX ports, as they were more common in later models with the rise of portable media devices like iPods and smartphones.\n\nHowever, there are aftermarket solutions available if you want to add an AUX input to your 2004 Passat. These include:\n\n1. **FM Transmitters**: These devices plug into the cigarette lighter and broadcast your music over an FM frequency that your car radio can pick up.\n2. **Cassette Adapters**: If your Passat has a cassette player, you can use a cassette adapter that connects to your device\u2019s headphone jack.\n3. **Aftermarket Stereo Systems**: You could replace the factory stereo with an aftermarket unit that includes an AUX port or even Bluetooth connectivity.\n4. **Wiring Kits**: Some kits allow you to integrate an AUX input into the factory stereo system, but this may require some technical knowledge or professional installation.\n\nIf you\u2019re unsure, consulting a car audio specialist can help you find the best solution for your needs.",
